main event: Sighting of a fast blue twinkling light in the Lincoln Park-Ecorse area.
interesting points: The object was observed both visually and on radar.
The object moved quickly from east to west in a straight line.
The object was visible for only about 2 minutes before going out of sight.
The report notes that the object would have been covered by a hatch head if not for its fast movement.
The report concludes the sighting was likely an astronomical or weather phenomenon, rather than an unidentified object.
result: Insufficient Information, Probably Astronomical or Weather Phenomena
